<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9326] ServerName is created using getLocalSocketAddress, breaks binding to the wildcard address. Revert HBASE-8640</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9326</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8148&quot; title=&quot;Allow IPC to bind on a specific address&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8148&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8148&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I added a way to bind to specific addresses, like 0.0.0.0, but right now in 0.95/trunk the ServerName is created using getLocalSocketAddress in RpcServer so 0.0.0.0 gets published in ZK.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
